# Docker Rules

## Required after code changes

After any change to `apps/**`, `docker-compose.yml`, or a `Dockerfile`, restart the full stack:

```bash
npm run docker:restart
```

Equivalent manual steps:

```bash
npm run docker:down
docker compose up --build -d
npm run docker:health
```

Do not finish a coding task without a successful health check unless the user opts out.

## Stack

`docker-compose.yml` at repo root:

| Service | Build context | Port |
|---------|---------------|------|
| mysql | mysql:8.4 image | 3306 |
| api | `apps/high-steak-api` | 8080 |
| web | `apps/high-steak-web` | 5173 |

## Key env vars

**API container:** `SPRING_DATASOURCE_*`, `JWT_SECRET`, `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS`, `UPLOADS_DIR`

**Web container:** `VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8080/api`

## Verification after rebuild

```bash
npm run docker:health
curl -s http://localhost:8080/api/health
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://localhost:8080/api/swagger-ui.html
```

## When to reset volumes

After incompatible Flyway migrations on an existing dev DB:

```bash
docker compose down -v
docker compose up --build -d
```

## Rebuild triggers

Rebuild API container when changing: `pom.xml`, `Dockerfile`, Java source, `application.yml`.

Rebuild web when changing: `Dockerfile`, env vars baked at build time for Vite.

## Examples

```yaml
# BAD — web pointing at host root without /api context
VITE_API_URL: http://localhost:8080

# GOOD
VITE_API_URL: http://localhost:8080/api
```

